{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841421209,"sessionID":"ses_2879ab85effeNL1ZUUbsvQv248","part":{"id":"prt_d7865a314001iGnnipbQmiBHfj","messageID":"msg_d786598a6001GVogkuqHiOeDkz","sessionID":"ses_2879ab85effeNL1ZUUbsvQv248","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_d9f49ecb07ea415fbe37c235","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the WorkloadManager HTTP service framework in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-004\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Scenario: HTTP Server Foundation\n17: \n18: ### AR-004-001: Server initialization\n19: \n20: - **GIVEN** a Go package at `pkg/workloadmanager`\n21: - **WHEN** creating HTTP server initialization\n22: - **THEN** the server SHALL embed necessary HTTP handlers\n23: - **AND** SHALL expose configurable listen address\n24: \n25: ### AR-004-002: Health check endpoint\n26: \n27: - **GIVEN** HTTP server running\n28: - **WHEN** health check endpoint is accessed\n29: - **THEN** it SHALL return appropriate health status\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## Scenario: Workload Management API\n34: \n35: ### AR-004-003: Create workload endpoint\n36: \n37: - **GIVEN** HTTP server with workload management\n38: - **WHEN** POST request to create workload\n39: - **THEN** the workload SHALL be created successfully\n40: \n41: ### AR-004-004: Get workload endpoint\n42: \n43: - **GIVEN** existing workloads\n44: - **WHEN** GET request for specific workload\n45: - **THEN** it SHALL return workload details\n46: \n47: ### AR-004-005: List workloads endpoint\n48: \n49: - **GIVEN** multiple workloads exist\n50: - **WHEN** GET request to list workloads\n51: - **THEN** it SHALL return all workloads\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## References\n\n(End of file - total 55 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the WorkloadManager HTTP service framework in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-004\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: HTTP Server Foundation\n\n### AR-004-001: Server initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** a Go package at `pkg/workloadmanager`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775841421193,"end":1775841421207}}}}
