{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841425162,"sessionID":"ses_2879ab85effeNL1ZUUbsvQv248","part":{"id":"prt_d7865b3160015fra6BDTx1JKJC","messageID":"msg_d7865a7cd001sgh1RNNgYOOGBO","sessionID":"ses_2879ab85effeNL1ZUUbsvQv248","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_bad97d4dfe61467680d6d759","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement an HTTP service framework in `pkg/workloadmanager` that exposes RESTful APIs for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter Kubernetes resources. The service integrates with the `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` library to provide CRUD operations and watch functionality.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: The WorkloadManager module needs to expose its functionality via HTTP APIs for external clients and internal services to interact with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in the Kubernetes cluster.\n11: \n12: ### Goal\n13: Provide a production-ready HTTP service framework that:\n14: - Serves RESTful APIs for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRUD operations\n15: - Integrates with the `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` library for Kubernetes API access\n16: - Follows Kubernetes controller patterns and best practices\n17: \n18: ### Value\n19: - Enables external systems to manage AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources programmatically\n20: - Provides a standardized HTTP interface layer on top of the Kubernetes client\n21: - Supports observability, middleware extensibility, and graceful shutdown\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## Scope\n26: \n27: ### In-Scope\n28: \n29: | Deliverable | Description |\n30: |-------------|-------------|\n31: | HTTP Server | Configurable host/port with graceful shutdown |\n32: | Health Endpoints | `/healthz`, `/readyz` for liveness/readiness probes |\n33: | REST API Endpoints | CRUD operations for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter |\n34: | Client Integration | Integration with client-go Clientset |\n35: | Middleware | Request logging, metrics, error handling |\n36: \n37: ### API Endpoints\n38: \n39: #### AgentRuntime\n40: | Method | Path | Description |\n41: |--------|------|-------------|\n42: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | List all AgentRuntimes |\n43: | POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | Create AgentRuntime |\n44: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Get AgentRuntime |\n45: | PUT | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Update AgentRuntime |\n46: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Delete AgentRuntime |\n47: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}/status` | Get AgentRuntime status |\n48: | PATCH | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}/status` | Patch AgentRuntime status |\n49: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes?watch=true` | Watch AgentRuntimes |\n50: \n51: #### CodeInterpreter\n52: | Method | Path | Description |\n53: |--------|------|-------------|\n54: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | List all CodeInterpreters |\n55: | POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | Create CodeInterpreter |\n56: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Get CodeInterpreter |\n57: | PUT | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Update CodeInterpreter |\n58: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Delete CodeInterpreter |\n59: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status` | Get CodeInterpreter status |\n60: | PATCH | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status` | Patch CodeInterpreter status |\n61: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters?watch=true` | Watch CodeInterpreters |\n62: \n63: ### Code Structure\n64: \n65: ```\n66: pkg/workloadmanager/\n67: ├── server.go                    # HTTP server implementation\n68: ├── router.go                    # Route definitions\n69: ├── handler/\n70: │   ├── agentruntime.go          # AgentRuntime handlers\n71: │   ├── codeinterpreter.go       # CodeInterpreter handlers\n72: │   └── handler.go               # Shared handler utilities\n73: ├── middleware/\n74: │   ├── logging.go               # Request logging\n75: │   ├── metrics.go               # Metrics collection\n76: │   └── error.go                 # Error handling\n77: ├── client/\n78: │   └── client.go                # Kubernetes client wrapper\n79: └── config/\n80:     └── config.go                # Server configuration\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ### Out-of-Scope\n84: - Custom Resource Definitions (CRDs) — already defined in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n85: - Controller/reconciler logic — separate concern\n86: - WebSocket or streaming APIs (beyond Kubernetes watch)\n87: - Authentication/Authorization (pluggable hooks only)\n88: - Rate limiting (future enhancement)\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ## Impact Analysis\n93: \n94: ### Dependencies\n95: \n96: | Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n97: |------------|--------|---------|\n98: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go | local | Kubernetes typed client |\n99: | k8s.io/client-go/rest | ^0.34 | Low-level REST client |\n100: | k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime | ^1.34 | Object serialization |\n101: | k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors | ^1.34 | Kubernetes API errors |\n102: | k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1 | ^1.34 | metav1 types |\n103: \n104: ### Downstream Consumers\n105: \n106: 1. **External CLI tools** — Manage AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter resources\n107: 2. **Webhook services** — Integrate with admission controllers\n108: 3. **Monitoring systems** — Query resource status via HTTP\n109: 4. **CI/CD pipelines** — Deploy workloads programmatically\n110: \n111: ### Risks\n112: \n113: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n114: |------|----------|------------|\n115: | Client resource leaks | High | Proper client lifecycle management |\n116: | API compatibility | Medium | Version prefixes for API stability |\n117: | Error propagation | Medium | Proper HTTP status code mapping |\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: ## Alternatives Considered\n122: \n123: ### Option 1: Standard Go net/http (Selected)\n124: \n125: **Approach**: Use Go's built-in `net/http` package for HTTP server implementation.\n126: \n127: **Pros**:\n128: - Full control over server behavior\n129: - No additional dependencies\n130: - Lightweight and minimal\n131: - Follows Kubernetes apiserver patterns\n132: \n133: **Cons**:\n134: - Must implement routing from scratch\n135: - Middleware must be built manually\n136: \n137: **Decision**: Selected for maximum flexibility and minimal dependencies.\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ### Option 2: Gin/Echo Framework\n142: \n143: **Approach**: Use third-party HTTP framework like Gin or Echo.\n144: \n145: **Pros**:\n146: - Rich routing capabilities\n147: - Built-in middleware ecosystem\n148: - Request validation helpers\n149: \n150: **Cons**:\n151: - Additional external dependency\n152: - Potential version drift\n153: - Overhead for simple use case\n154: \n155: **Decision**: Rejected — adds unnecessary complexity for Kubernetes controller context.\n156: \n157: ---\n158: \n159: ### Option 3: Kubernetes API Server Aggregation\n160: \n161: **Approach**: Implement as Kubernetes API server aggregation layer.\n162: \n163: **Pros**:\n164: - Native Kubernetes integration\n165: - Built-in authentication/authorization\n166: - Standard Kubernetes client compatibility\n167: \n168: **Cons**:\n169: - Complex setup and configuration\n170: - Requires API server configuration\n171: - Higher resource footprint\n172: \n173: **Decision**: Rejected — separate feature, not within current scope.\n174: \n175: ---\n176: \n177: ### Option 4: gRPC with grpc-gateway\n178: \n179: **Approach**: Use gRPC for internal communication with grpc-gateway for REST.\n180: \n181: **Pros**:\n182: - Type-safe service definitions\n183: - Streaming support\n184: - High performance\n185: \n186: **Cons**:\n187: - Requires protobuf definitions\n188: - Additional complexity\n189: - gRPC not required for current use case\n190: \n191: **Decision**: Rejected — gRPC not required for current HTTP API requirements.\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ## Implementation Plan\n196: \n197: ### Phase 1: Core Server\n198: - [ ] Implement `server.go` with configurable host/port\n199: - [ ] Add graceful shutdown handling\n200: - [ ] Create health check endpoints (`/healthz`, `/readyz`)\n201: \n202: ### Phase 2: Client Integration\n203: - [ ] Create Kubernetes client wrapper in `client/client.go`\n204: - [ ] Integrate with client-go `Clientset`\n205: - [ ] Handle config loading (in-cluster, kubeconfig)\n206: \n207: ### Phase 3: Router & Handlers\n208: - [ ] Implement `router.go` with route definitions\n209: - [ ] Create AgentRuntime handlers\n210: - [ ] Create CodeInterpreter handlers\n211: - [ ] Add list/watch support\n212: \n213: ### Phase 4: Middleware\n214: - [ ] Add request logging middleware\n215: - [ ] Add metrics collection\n216: - [ ] Implement error handling middleware\n217: \n218: ### Phase 5: Testing\n219: - [ ] Unit tests for handlers\n220: - [ ] Integration tests with fake clientset\n221: - [ ] End-to-end tests against mock API server\n222: \n223: ---\n224: \n225: ## Acceptance Criteria\n226: \n227: - [ ] HTTP server starts and listens on configured port\n228: - [ ] Health endpoints (`/healthz`, `/readyz`) return 200 OK\n229: - [ ] All CRUD operations for AgentRuntime work correctly\n230: - [ ] All CRUD operations for CodeInterpreter work correctly\n231: - [ ] Watch endpoints stream properly\n232: - [ ] Kubernetes client is properly managed (no resource leaks)\n233: - [ ] Request logging captures relevant details\n234: - [ ] Errors are properly mapped to HTTP status codes\n235: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage for handlers\n236: - [ ] Server handles graceful shutdown within 30 seconds\n\n(End of file - total 236 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement an HTTP service framework in `pkg/workloadmanager` that exposes RESTful APIs for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter Kubernetes resources. The service integrates with the `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` library to provide CRUD operations and watch functionality.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\nThe WorkloadManager module needs to expose its functionality via HTTP APIs for external clients and internal services to interact with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in the Kubernetes cluster.\n\n### Goal\nProvide a production-ready HTTP service framework that:\n- Serves RESTful APIs for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRUD operations\n- Integrates with the `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` library for Kubernetes API access\n- Follows Kubernetes controller patterns and best practices\n\n### Value\n- Enables external systems to manage AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources programmatically\n- Provides a standardized HTTP interface layer on top of the Kubernetes client","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775841425151,"end":1775841425159}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775841425192,"sessionID":"ses_2879ab85effeNL1ZUUbsvQv248","part":{"id":"prt_d7865b7090018H4GveV7RqhvZl","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7865a7cd001sgh1RNNgYOOGBO","sessionID":"ses_2879ab85effeNL1ZUUbsvQv248","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":22725,"input":640,"output":125,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":21960}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775841428224,"sessionID":"ses_2879ab85effeNL1ZUUbsvQv248","part":{"id":"prt_d7865c2ff001jXzGxOUXAw7U2K","messageID":"msg_d7865b73d001AlF0O3SvewIpNQ","sessionID":"ses_2879ab85effeNL1ZUUbsvQv248","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775841431598,"sessionID":"ses_2879ab85effeNL1ZUUbsvQv248","part":{"id":"prt_d7865caa600114QqAvvuzEdV44","messageID":"msg_d7865b73d001AlF0O3SvewIpNQ","sessionID":"ses_2879ab85effeNL1ZUUbsvQv248","type":"text","text":"Now I have full context. Let me expand the delta-spec.md with comprehensive GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios based on the proposal and client-go specs:","time":{"start":1775841431595,"end":1775841431595}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841496658,"sessionID":"ses_2879ab85effeNL1ZUUbsvQv248","part":{"id":"prt_d7865d02f001MoFRzFPVUUtFOk","messageID":"msg_d7865b73d001AlF0O3SvewIpNQ","sessionID":"ses_2879ab85effeNL1ZUUbsvQv248","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_dd2cb63150cd487aa2137829","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md","newString":"# Delta Spec: AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the WorkloadManager HTTP service framework in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-004\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Depends On**: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` (clientset, informers, listers)\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: HTTP Server Foundation\n\n### AR-004-001: Server initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** a Go package at `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **WHEN** creating HTTP server initialization\n- **THEN** the server SHALL embed necessary HTTP handlers\n- **AND** SHALL expose configurable listen address via `--port` flag (default 8080)\n- **AND** SHALL support graceful shutdown within 30 seconds\n\n### AR-004-002: Health check endpoints\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server running on configured port\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/healthz`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with status \"ok\"\n- **AND** SHALL return Content-Type `text/plain`\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server running on configured port\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/readyz`\n- - **THEN** it SHALL return HTTP 200 OK when server is ready to serve traffic\n- **AND** it SHALL return HTTP 503 Service Unavailable when not ready\n\n### AR-004-003: Server configuration via flags\n\n- **GIVEN** workloadmanager binary with flag parsing\n- **WHEN** started with `--port=9090`\n- **THEN** the HTTP server SHALL listen on port 9090\n\n- **GIVEN** workloadmanager binary\n- **WHEN** started with no flags\n- **THEN** it SHALL use default port 8080\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Kubernetes Client Integration\n\n### AR-004-010: Client initialization from kubeconfig\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig file at default location (`~/.kube/config`)\n- **WHEN** creating Kubernetes client via `client.NewForConfig`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a Clientset with RuntimeV1alpha1() accessor\n- **AND** SHALL be able to communicate with the Kubernetes API server\n\n### AR-004-011: Client initialization in-cluster\n\n- **GIVEN** running inside a Kubernetes pod with ServiceAccount mounted\n- **WHEN** creating Kubernetes client via `rest.InClusterConfig()`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a Clientset with credentials from the ServiceAccount\n- **AND** SHALL be able to communicate with the Kubernetes API server\n\n### AR-004-012: Client resource cleanup\n\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes Clientset is created\n- **WHEN** the server shuts down gracefully\n- **THEN** all HTTP clients SHALL be properly closed\n- **AND** SHALL not leak goroutines or connections\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: AgentRuntime CRUD API\n\n### AR-004-020: Create AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server with Kubernetes client connected to a cluster with AgentRuntime CRD\n- **WHEN** client sends POST request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes` with valid AgentRuntime JSON body\n- **THEN** the server SHALL create the AgentRuntime resource in Kubernetes\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 201 Created with the created resource in response body\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends POST request with invalid AgentRuntime JSON\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request with error details\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends POST request to non-existent namespace\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n\n### AR-004-021: Get AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-runtime\" in namespace \"default\"\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the AgentRuntime resource as JSON\n- **AND** the response SHALL include the complete resource with metadata and spec\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request for non-existent AgentRuntime\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n\n### AR-004-022: List AgentRuntimes\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple AgentRuntime resources exist in namespace \"default\"\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with an AgentRuntimeList containing all matching resources\n- **AND** SHALL support `labelSelector` query parameter for filtering\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to non-existent namespace\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n\n### AR-004-023: Update AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-runtime\" in namespace \"default\"\n- **WHEN** client sends PUT request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime` with updated AgentRuntime JSON\n- **THEN** the server SHALL update the AgentRuntime resource in Kubernetes\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the updated resource\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends PUT request with mismatched name in body and URL\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request\n\n### AR-004-024: Delete AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-runtime\" in namespace \"default\"\n- **WHEN** client sends DELETE request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL delete the AgentRuntime resource from Kubernetes\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the deleted resource\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends DELETE request for non-existent AgentRuntime\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n\n### AR-004-025: Get AgentRuntime status\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime with status field populated\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime/status`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the AgentRuntime status\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request for status subresource of non-existent AgentRuntime\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n\n### AR-004-026: Patch AgentRuntime status\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime\n- **WHEN** client sends PATCH request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime/status` with JSON Patch\n- **THEN** the server SHALL patch only the status field of the AgentRuntime\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the patched resource\n\n### AR-004-027: Watch AgentRuntimes\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple AgentRuntime resources exist\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes?watch=true`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n- **AND** SHALL stream WATCH_EVENT objects as newline-delimited JSON (NDJSON)\n- **AND** SHALL send ADDED, MODIFIED, and DELETED events as resources change\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRUD API\n\n### AR-004-030: Create CodeInterpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server with Kubernetes client connected to a cluster with CodeInterpreter CRD\n- **WHEN** client sends POST request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters` with valid CodeInterpreter JSON body\n- **THEN** the server SHALL create the CodeInterpreter resource in Kubernetes\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 201 Created with the created resource in response body\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends POST request with invalid CodeInterpreter JSON\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request with error details\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends POST request to non-existent namespace\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n\n### AR-004-031: Get CodeInterpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter named \"test-interpreter\" in namespace \"default\"\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters/test-interpreter`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the CodeInterpreter resource as JSON\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request for non-existent CodeInterpreter\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n\n### AR-004-032: List CodeInterpreters\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple CodeInterpreter resources exist in namespace \"default\"\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with a CodeInterpreterList containing all matching resources\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request with `labelSelector` query parameter\n- **THEN** the server SHALL filter results by the specified label selector\n\n### AR-004-033: Update CodeInterpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter\n- **WHEN** client sends PUT request with updated CodeInterpreter JSON\n- **THEN** the server SHALL update the CodeInterpreter resource in Kubernetes\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the updated resource\n\n### AR-004-034: Delete CodeInterpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter\n- **WHEN** client sends DELETE request\n- **THEN** the server SHALL delete the CodeInterpreter resource\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the deleted resource\n\n### AR-004-035: Get CodeInterpreter status\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter with status field populated\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the CodeInterpreter status\n\n### AR-004-036: Patch CodeInterpreter status\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter\n- **WHEN** client sends PATCH request to status subresource\n- **THEN** the server SHALL patch only the status field\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the patched resource\n\n### AR-004-037: Watch CodeInterpreters\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple CodeInterpreter resources exist\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters?watch=true`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL stream WATCH_EVENT objects as NDJSON\n- **AND** SHALL send ADDED, MODIFIED, and DELETED events\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Middleware & Observability\n\n### AR-004-040: Request logging middleware\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server with logging middleware configured\n- **WHEN** any HTTP request is received\n- **THEN** the server SHALL log the request method, path, status code, and latency\n- **AND** SHALL log at appropriate level (info for success, error for 5xx)\n\n### AR-004-041: Metrics collection\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server with metrics middleware\n- **WHEN** HTTP requests are processed\n- **THEN** the server SHALL track request count by method and path\n- **AND** SHALL track request duration histogram\n- **AND** SHALL track response status code distribution\n\n### AR-004-042: Error handling middleware\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server with error handling middleware\n- **WHEN** a handler returns an error\n- **THEN** the server SHALL map Kubernetes API errors to appropriate HTTP status codes\n- **AND** SHALL return structured error response with message and details\n- **AND** SHALL log the error with appropriate context\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: API Format & Compatibility\n\n### AR-004-050: JSON content type\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends request with `Accept: application/json`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return responses with `Content-Type: application/json`\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends POST/PUT/PATCH request with `Content-Type: application/json`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL parse the request body as JSON\n\n### AR-004-051: Error response format\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server returning an error\n- **WHEN** error occurs during request processing\n- **THEN** the response SHALL be a JSON object with `kind` = \"Status\", `apiVersion` = \"v1\", `status` = \"Failure\"\n- **AND** SHALL include `message`, `reason`, and `code` fields\n- **AND** SHALL follow Kubernetes API error format\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Integration with client-go\n\n### AR-004-060: Use RuntimeV1alpha1 Clientset\n\n- **GIVEN** a configured Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** accessing AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter resources\n- **THEN** the server SHALL use the `RuntimeV1alpha1()` accessor from the Clientset\n- **AND** SHALL use typed clients for all CRUD operations\n\n### AR-004-061: Use Informers for read operations\n\n- **GIVEN** a SharedInformerFactory is configured\n- **WHEN** serving list requests\n- **THEN** the server SHOULD use the Informer cache for faster responses\n- **AND** SHALL fall back to direct API calls if cache is not ready\n\n### AR-004-062: Use Listers for cached reads\n\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeLister is available\n- **WHEN** serving GET/List requests for AgentRuntime\n- **THEN** the server SHALL use the Lister for cached reads\n- **AND** SHALL return consistent data from the cache\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: ClusterRole & RBAC\n\n### AR-004-070: Required RBAC permissions\n\n- **GIVEN** WorkloadManager deployed with ServiceAccount\n- **WHEN** making API calls to Kubernetes\n- **THEN** the ServiceAccount SHALL have permissions to create, get, list, update, patch, delete, and watch AgentRuntime resources\n- **AND** SHALL have permissions to create, get, list, update, patch, delete, and watch CodeInterpreter resources\n- **AND** SHALL have permissions to list/watch pods and events in relevant namespaces\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- client-go library: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n- AgentRuntime CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n- CodeInterpreter CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n- API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`","oldString":"# Delta Spec: AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the WorkloadManager HTTP service framework in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-004\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: HTTP Server Foundation\n\n### AR-004-001: Server initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** a Go package at `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **WHEN** creating HTTP server initialization\n- **THEN** the server SHALL embed necessary HTTP handlers\n- **AND** SHALL expose configurable listen address\n\n### AR-004-002: Health check endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server running\n- **WHEN** health check endpoint is accessed\n- **THEN** it SHALL return appropriate health status\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Workload Management API\n\n### AR-004-003: Create workload endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server with workload management\n- **WHEN** POST request to create workload\n- **THEN** the workload SHALL be created successfully\n\n### AR-004-004: Get workload endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** existing workloads\n- **WHEN** GET request for specific workload\n- **THEN** it SHALL return workload details\n\n### AR-004-005: List workloads endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple workloads exist\n- **WHEN** GET request to list workloads\n- **THEN** it SHALL return all workloads\n\n---\n\n## References"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md\n@@ -9,8 +9,9 @@\n - **AR**: AR-004\n - **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n - **Language**: Go\n - **Size**: M\n+- **Depends On**: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` (clientset, informers, listers)\n \n ---\n \n ## Scenario: HTTP Server Foundation\n@@ -19,37 +20,309 @@\n \n - **GIVEN** a Go package at `pkg/workloadmanager`\n - **WHEN** creating HTTP server initialization\n - **THEN** the server SHALL embed necessary HTTP handlers\n-- **AND** SHALL expose configurable listen address\n+- **AND** SHALL expose configurable listen address via `--port` flag (default 8080)\n+- **AND** SHALL support graceful shutdown within 30 seconds\n \n-### AR-004-002: Health check endpoint\n+### AR-004-002: Health check endpoints\n \n-- **GIVEN** HTTP server running\n-- **WHEN** health check endpoint is accessed\n-- **THEN** it SHALL return appropriate health status\n+- **GIVEN** HTTP server running on configured port\n+- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/healthz`\n+- **THEN** it SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with status \"ok\"\n+- **AND** SHALL return Content-Type `text/plain`\n \n+- **GIVEN** HTTP server running on configured port\n+- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/readyz`\n+- - **THEN** it SHALL return HTTP 200 OK when server is ready to serve traffic\n+- **AND** it SHALL return HTTP 503 Service Unavailable when not ready\n+\n+### AR-004-003: Server configuration via flags\n+\n+- **GIVEN** workloadmanager binary with flag parsing\n+- **WHEN** started with `--port=9090`\n+- **THEN** the HTTP server SHALL listen on port 9090\n+\n+- **GIVEN** workloadmanager binary\n+- **WHEN** started with no flags\n+- **THEN** it SHALL use default port 8080\n+\n ---\n \n-## Scenario: Workload Management API\n+## Scenario: Kubernetes Client Integration\n \n-### AR-004-003: Create workload endpoint\n+### AR-004-010: Client initialization from kubeconfig\n \n-- **GIVEN** HTTP server with workload management\n-- **WHEN** POST request to create workload\n-- **THEN** the workload SHALL be created successfully\n+- **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig file at default location (`~/.kube/config`)\n+- **WHEN** creating Kubernetes client via `client.NewForConfig`\n+- **THEN** it SHALL return a Clientset with RuntimeV1alpha1() accessor\n+- **AND** SHALL be able to communicate with the Kubernetes API server\n \n-### AR-004-004: Get workload endpoint\n+### AR-004-011: Client initialization in-cluster\n \n-- **GIVEN** existing workloads\n-- **WHEN** GET request for specific workload\n-- **THEN** it SHALL return workload details\n+- **GIVEN** running inside a Kubernetes pod with ServiceAccount mounted\n+- **WHEN** creating Kubernetes client via `rest.InClusterConfig()`\n+- **THEN** it SHALL return a Clientset with credentials from the ServiceAccount\n+- **AND** SHALL be able to communicate with the Kubernetes API server\n \n-### AR-004-005: List workloads endpoint\n+### AR-004-012: Client resource cleanup\n \n-- **GIVEN** multiple workloads exist\n-- **WHEN** GET request to list workloads\n-- **THEN** it SHALL return all workloads\n+- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes Clientset is created\n+- **WHEN** the server shuts down gracefully\n+- **THEN** all HTTP clients SHALL be properly closed\n+- **AND** SHALL not leak goroutines or connections\n \n ---\n \n+## Scenario: AgentRuntime CRUD API\n+\n+### AR-004-020: Create AgentRuntime\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server with Kubernetes client connected to a cluster with AgentRuntime CRD\n+- **WHEN** client sends POST request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes` with valid AgentRuntime JSON body\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL create the AgentRuntime resource in Kubernetes\n+- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 201 Created with the created resource in response body\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n+- **WHEN** client sends POST request with invalid AgentRuntime JSON\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request with error details\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n+- **WHEN** client sends POST request to non-existent namespace\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n+\n+### AR-004-021: Get AgentRuntime\n+\n+- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-runtime\" in namespace \"default\"\n+- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime`\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the AgentRuntime resource as JSON\n+- **AND** the response SHALL include the complete resource with metadata and spec\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n+- **WHEN** client sends GET request for non-existent AgentRuntime\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n+\n+### AR-004-022: List AgentRuntimes\n+\n+- **GIVEN** multiple AgentRuntime resources exist in namespace \"default\"\n+- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes`\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with an AgentRuntimeList containing all matching resources\n+- **AND** SHALL support `labelSelector` query parameter for filtering\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n+- **WHEN** client sends GET request to non-existent namespace\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n+\n+### AR-004-023: Update AgentRuntime\n+\n+- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-runtime\" in namespace \"default\"\n+- **WHEN** client sends PUT request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime` with updated AgentRuntime JSON\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL update the AgentRuntime resource in Kubernetes\n+- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the updated resource\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n+- **WHEN** client sends PUT request with mismatched name in body and URL\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request\n+\n+### AR-004-024: Delete AgentRuntime\n+\n+- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-runtime\" in namespace \"default\"\n+- **WHEN** client sends DELETE request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime`\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL delete the AgentRuntime resource from Kubernetes\n+- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the deleted resource\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n+- **WHEN** client sends DELETE request for non-existent AgentRuntime\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n+\n+### AR-004-025: Get AgentRuntime status\n+\n+- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime with status field populated\n+- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime/status`\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the AgentRuntime status\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n+- **WHEN** client sends GET request for status subresource of non-existent AgentRuntime\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n+\n+### AR-004-026: Patch AgentRuntime status\n+\n+- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime\n+- **WHEN** client sends PATCH request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime/status` with JSON Patch\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL patch only the status field of the AgentRuntime\n+- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the patched resource\n+\n+### AR-004-027: Watch AgentRuntimes\n+\n+- **GIVEN** multiple AgentRuntime resources exist\n+- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes?watch=true`\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n+- **AND** SHALL stream WATCH_EVENT objects as newline-delimited JSON (NDJSON)\n+- **AND** SHALL send ADDED, MODIFIED, and DELETED events as resources change\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRUD API\n+\n+### AR-004-030: Create CodeInterpreter\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server with Kubernetes client connected to a cluster with CodeInterpreter CRD\n+- **WHEN** client sends POST request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters` with valid CodeInterpreter JSON body\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL create the CodeInterpreter resource in Kubernetes\n+- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 201 Created with the created resource in response body\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n+- **WHEN** client sends POST request with invalid CodeInterpreter JSON\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request with error details\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n+- **WHEN** client sends POST request to non-existent namespace\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n+\n+### AR-004-031: Get CodeInterpreter\n+\n+- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter named \"test-interpreter\" in namespace \"default\"\n+- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters/test-interpreter`\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the CodeInterpreter resource as JSON\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n+- **WHEN** client sends GET request for non-existent CodeInterpreter\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n+\n+### AR-004-032: List CodeInterpreters\n+\n+- **GIVEN** multiple CodeInterpreter resources exist in namespace \"default\"\n+- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters`\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with a CodeInterpreterList containing all matching resources\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n+- **WHEN** client sends GET request with `labelSelector` query parameter\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL filter results by the specified label selector\n+\n+### AR-004-033: Update CodeInterpreter\n+\n+- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter\n+- **WHEN** client sends PUT request with updated CodeInterpreter JSON\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL update the CodeInterpreter resource in Kubernetes\n+- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the updated resource\n+\n+### AR-004-034: Delete CodeInterpreter\n+\n+- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter\n+- **WHEN** client sends DELETE request\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL delete the CodeInterpreter resource\n+- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the deleted resource\n+\n+### AR-004-035: Get CodeInterpreter status\n+\n+- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter with status field populated\n+- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status`\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the CodeInterpreter status\n+\n+### AR-004-036: Patch CodeInterpreter status\n+\n+- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter\n+- **WHEN** client sends PATCH request to status subresource\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL patch only the status field\n+- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the patched resource\n+\n+### AR-004-037: Watch CodeInterpreters\n+\n+- **GIVEN** multiple CodeInterpreter resources exist\n+- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters?watch=true`\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL stream WATCH_EVENT objects as NDJSON\n+- **AND** SHALL send ADDED, MODIFIED, and DELETED events\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Scenario: Middleware & Observability\n+\n+### AR-004-040: Request logging middleware\n+\n+- **GIVEN** HTTP server with logging middleware configured\n+- **WHEN** any HTTP request is received\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL log the request method, path, status code, and latency\n+- **AND** SHALL log at appropriate level (info for success, error for 5xx)\n+\n+### AR-004-041: Metrics collection\n+\n+- **GIVEN** HTTP server with metrics middleware\n+- **WHEN** HTTP requests are processed\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL track request count by method and path\n+- **AND** SHALL track request duration histogram\n+- **AND** SHALL track response status code distribution\n+\n+### AR-004-042: Error handling middleware\n+\n+- **GIVEN** HTTP server with error handling middleware\n+- **WHEN** a handler returns an error\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL map Kubernetes API errors to appropriate HTTP status codes\n+- **AND** SHALL return structured error response with message and details\n+- **AND** SHALL log the error with appropriate context\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Scenario: API Format & Compatibility\n+\n+### AR-004-050: JSON content type\n+\n+- **GIVEN** HTTP server\n+- **WHEN** client sends request with `Accept: application/json`\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL return responses with `Content-Type: application/json`\n+\n+- **GIVEN** HTTP server\n+- **WHEN** client sends POST/PUT/PATCH request with `Content-Type: application/json`\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL parse the request body as JSON\n+\n+### AR-004-051: Error response format\n+\n+- **GIVEN** HTTP server returning an error\n+- **WHEN** error occurs during request processing\n+- **THEN** the response SHALL be a JSON object with `kind` = \"Status\", `apiVersion` = \"v1\", `status` = \"Failure\"\n+- **AND** SHALL include `message`, `reason`, and `code` fields\n+- **AND** SHALL follow Kubernetes API error format\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Scenario: Integration with client-go\n+\n+### AR-004-060: Use RuntimeV1alpha1 Clientset\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a configured Kubernetes client\n+- **WHEN** accessing AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter resources\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL use the `RuntimeV1alpha1()` accessor from the Clientset\n+- **AND** SHALL use typed clients for all CRUD operations\n+\n+### AR-004-061: Use Informers for read operations\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a SharedInformerFactory is configured\n+- **WHEN** serving list requests\n+- **THEN** the server SHOULD use the Informer cache for faster responses\n+- **AND** SHALL fall back to direct API calls if cache is not ready\n+\n+### AR-004-062: Use Listers for cached reads\n+\n+- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeLister is available\n+- **WHEN** serving GET/List requests for AgentRuntime\n+- **THEN** the server SHALL use the Lister for cached reads\n+- **AND** SHALL return consistent data from the cache\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Scenario: ClusterRole & RBAC\n+\n+### AR-004-070: Required RBAC permissions\n+\n+- **GIVEN** WorkloadManager deployed with ServiceAccount\n+- **WHEN** making API calls to Kubernetes\n+- **THEN** the ServiceAccount SHALL have permissions to create, get, list, update, patch, delete, and watch AgentRuntime resources\n+- **AND** SHALL have permissions to create, get, list, update, patch, delete, and watch CodeInterpreter resources\n+- **AND** SHALL have permissions to list/watch pods and events in relevant namespaces\n+\n+---\n+\n ## References\n+\n+- client-go library: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n+- AgentRuntime CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n+- CodeInterpreter CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n+- API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md","before":"# Delta Spec: AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the WorkloadManager HTTP service framework in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-004\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: HTTP Server Foundation\n\n### AR-004-001: Server initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** a Go package at `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **WHEN** creating HTTP server initialization\n- **THEN** the server SHALL embed necessary HTTP handlers\n- **AND** SHALL expose configurable listen address\n\n### AR-004-002: Health check endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server running\n- **WHEN** health check endpoint is accessed\n- **THEN** it SHALL return appropriate health status\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Workload Management API\n\n### AR-004-003: Create workload endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server with workload management\n- **WHEN** POST request to create workload\n- **THEN** the workload SHALL be created successfully\n\n### AR-004-004: Get workload endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** existing workloads\n- **WHEN** GET request for specific workload\n- **THEN** it SHALL return workload details\n\n### AR-004-005: List workloads endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple workloads exist\n- **WHEN** GET request to list workloads\n- **THEN** it SHALL return all workloads\n\n---\n\n## References\n","after":"# Delta Spec: AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the WorkloadManager HTTP service framework in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-004\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Depends On**: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` (clientset, informers, listers)\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: HTTP Server Foundation\n\n### AR-004-001: Server initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** a Go package at `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **WHEN** creating HTTP server initialization\n- **THEN** the server SHALL embed necessary HTTP handlers\n- **AND** SHALL expose configurable listen address via `--port` flag (default 8080)\n- **AND** SHALL support graceful shutdown within 30 seconds\n\n### AR-004-002: Health check endpoints\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server running on configured port\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/healthz`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with status \"ok\"\n- **AND** SHALL return Content-Type `text/plain`\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server running on configured port\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/readyz`\n- - **THEN** it SHALL return HTTP 200 OK when server is ready to serve traffic\n- **AND** it SHALL return HTTP 503 Service Unavailable when not ready\n\n### AR-004-003: Server configuration via flags\n\n- **GIVEN** workloadmanager binary with flag parsing\n- **WHEN** started with `--port=9090`\n- **THEN** the HTTP server SHALL listen on port 9090\n\n- **GIVEN** workloadmanager binary\n- **WHEN** started with no flags\n- **THEN** it SHALL use default port 8080\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Kubernetes Client Integration\n\n### AR-004-010: Client initialization from kubeconfig\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig file at default location (`~/.kube/config`)\n- **WHEN** creating Kubernetes client via `client.NewForConfig`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a Clientset with RuntimeV1alpha1() accessor\n- **AND** SHALL be able to communicate with the Kubernetes API server\n\n### AR-004-011: Client initialization in-cluster\n\n- **GIVEN** running inside a Kubernetes pod with ServiceAccount mounted\n- **WHEN** creating Kubernetes client via `rest.InClusterConfig()`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a Clientset with credentials from the ServiceAccount\n- **AND** SHALL be able to communicate with the Kubernetes API server\n\n### AR-004-012: Client resource cleanup\n\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes Clientset is created\n- **WHEN** the server shuts down gracefully\n- **THEN** all HTTP clients SHALL be properly closed\n- **AND** SHALL not leak goroutines or connections\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: AgentRuntime CRUD API\n\n### AR-004-020: Create AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server with Kubernetes client connected to a cluster with AgentRuntime CRD\n- **WHEN** client sends POST request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes` with valid AgentRuntime JSON body\n- **THEN** the server SHALL create the AgentRuntime resource in Kubernetes\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 201 Created with the created resource in response body\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends POST request with invalid AgentRuntime JSON\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request with error details\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends POST request to non-existent namespace\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n\n### AR-004-021: Get AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-runtime\" in namespace \"default\"\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the AgentRuntime resource as JSON\n- **AND** the response SHALL include the complete resource with metadata and spec\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request for non-existent AgentRuntime\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n\n### AR-004-022: List AgentRuntimes\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple AgentRuntime resources exist in namespace \"default\"\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with an AgentRuntimeList containing all matching resources\n- **AND** SHALL support `labelSelector` query parameter for filtering\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to non-existent namespace\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n\n### AR-004-023: Update AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-runtime\" in namespace \"default\"\n- **WHEN** client sends PUT request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime` with updated AgentRuntime JSON\n- **THEN** the server SHALL update the AgentRuntime resource in Kubernetes\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the updated resource\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends PUT request with mismatched name in body and URL\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request\n\n### AR-004-024: Delete AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-runtime\" in namespace \"default\"\n- **WHEN** client sends DELETE request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL delete the AgentRuntime resource from Kubernetes\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the deleted resource\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends DELETE request for non-existent AgentRuntime\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n\n### AR-004-025: Get AgentRuntime status\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime with status field populated\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime/status`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the AgentRuntime status\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request for status subresource of non-existent AgentRuntime\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n\n### AR-004-026: Patch AgentRuntime status\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime\n- **WHEN** client sends PATCH request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime/status` with JSON Patch\n- **THEN** the server SHALL patch only the status field of the AgentRuntime\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the patched resource\n\n### AR-004-027: Watch AgentRuntimes\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple AgentRuntime resources exist\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes?watch=true`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n- **AND** SHALL stream WATCH_EVENT objects as newline-delimited JSON (NDJSON)\n- **AND** SHALL send ADDED, MODIFIED, and DELETED events as resources change\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRUD API\n\n### AR-004-030: Create CodeInterpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server with Kubernetes client connected to a cluster with CodeInterpreter CRD\n- **WHEN** client sends POST request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters` with valid CodeInterpreter JSON body\n- **THEN** the server SHALL create the CodeInterpreter resource in Kubernetes\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 201 Created with the created resource in response body\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends POST request with invalid CodeInterpreter JSON\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request with error details\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends POST request to non-existent namespace\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n\n### AR-004-031: Get CodeInterpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter named \"test-interpreter\" in namespace \"default\"\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters/test-interpreter`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the CodeInterpreter resource as JSON\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request for non-existent CodeInterpreter\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n\n### AR-004-032: List CodeInterpreters\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple CodeInterpreter resources exist in namespace \"default\"\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with a CodeInterpreterList containing all matching resources\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request with `labelSelector` query parameter\n- **THEN** the server SHALL filter results by the specified label selector\n\n### AR-004-033: Update CodeInterpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter\n- **WHEN** client sends PUT request with updated CodeInterpreter JSON\n- **THEN** the server SHALL update the CodeInterpreter resource in Kubernetes\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the updated resource\n\n### AR-004-034: Delete CodeInterpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter\n- **WHEN** client sends DELETE request\n- **THEN** the server SHALL delete the CodeInterpreter resource\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the deleted resource\n\n### AR-004-035: Get CodeInterpreter status\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter with status field populated\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the CodeInterpreter status\n\n### AR-004-036: Patch CodeInterpreter status\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter\n- **WHEN** client sends PATCH request to status subresource\n- **THEN** the server SHALL patch only the status field\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the patched resource\n\n### AR-004-037: Watch CodeInterpreters\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple CodeInterpreter resources exist\n- **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters?watch=true`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL stream WATCH_EVENT objects as NDJSON\n- **AND** SHALL send ADDED, MODIFIED, and DELETED events\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Middleware & Observability\n\n### AR-004-040: Request logging middleware\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server with logging middleware configured\n- **WHEN** any HTTP request is received\n- **THEN** the server SHALL log the request method, path, status code, and latency\n- **AND** SHALL log at appropriate level (info for success, error for 5xx)\n\n### AR-004-041: Metrics collection\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server with metrics middleware\n- **WHEN** HTTP requests are processed\n- **THEN** the server SHALL track request count by method and path\n- **AND** SHALL track request duration histogram\n- **AND** SHALL track response status code distribution\n\n### AR-004-042: Error handling middleware\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server with error handling middleware\n- **WHEN** a handler returns an error\n- **THEN** the server SHALL map Kubernetes API errors to appropriate HTTP status codes\n- **AND** SHALL return structured error response with message and details\n- **AND** SHALL log the error with appropriate context\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: API Format & Compatibility\n\n### AR-004-050: JSON content type\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends request with `Accept: application/json`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return responses with `Content-Type: application/json`\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server\n- **WHEN** client sends POST/PUT/PATCH request with `Content-Type: application/json`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL parse the request body as JSON\n\n### AR-004-051: Error response format\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server returning an error\n- **WHEN** error occurs during request processing\n- **THEN** the response SHALL be a JSON object with `kind` = \"Status\", `apiVersion` = \"v1\", `status` = \"Failure\"\n- **AND** SHALL include `message`, `reason`, and `code` fields\n- **AND** SHALL follow Kubernetes API error format\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Integration with client-go\n\n### AR-004-060: Use RuntimeV1alpha1 Clientset\n\n- **GIVEN** a configured Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** accessing AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter resources\n- **THEN** the server SHALL use the `RuntimeV1alpha1()` accessor from the Clientset\n- **AND** SHALL use typed clients for all CRUD operations\n\n### AR-004-061: Use Informers for read operations\n\n- **GIVEN** a SharedInformerFactory is configured\n- **WHEN** serving list requests\n- **THEN** the server SHOULD use the Informer cache for faster responses\n- **AND** SHALL fall back to direct API calls if cache is not ready\n\n### AR-004-062: Use Listers for cached reads\n\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeLister is available\n- **WHEN** serving GET/List requests for AgentRuntime\n- **THEN** the server SHALL use the Lister for cached reads\n- **AND** SHALL return consistent data from the cache\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: ClusterRole & RBAC\n\n### AR-004-070: Required RBAC permissions\n\n- **GIVEN** WorkloadManager deployed with ServiceAccount\n- **WHEN** making API calls to Kubernetes\n- **THEN** the ServiceAccount SHALL have permissions to create, get, list, update, patch, delete, and watch AgentRuntime resources\n- **AND** SHALL have permissions to create, get, list, update, patch, delete, and watch CodeInterpreter resources\n- **AND** SHALL have permissions to list/watch pods and events in relevant namespaces\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- client-go library: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n- AgentRuntime CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n- CodeInterpreter CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n- API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n","additions":291,"deletions":18},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775841496610,"end":1775841496654}}}}
